SEARCH
Package interpreter

Class jqs

java.lang.Object
interpreter.jqs
public class jqs extends Object
This class provides the user interface for jqsim. The commands are similar to other established quantum simulator libraries.
The jqs constructor is overloaded, you can provide the number of shots as the 2nd parameter if you desire a different number of shots than the default of 1024.
    Phi values: as a double. Control values: as an integer of which qubit to use as control. Target values: as an integer of which qubit to use as the target.
    For multi-qubit gates, provide an array of int for controls and an array of int[] as targets.

This class instantiates a StateTracker which tracks the system vector as the system state as a column vector of the qubit amplitudes. It also instantiates the WorkQueue which processes the gates applied to each qubit as the user defines.
Since:
7 July 2024
Version:

Author:
